==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monocotyledon
<hw>Mon`o*cot`y*le"don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + <ets>cotyledon</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>monocotyl⟦eacute⟧done</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant
with only one cotyledon, or seed lobe; a member of the
<class>Monocotyledonae</class>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The plural, <xex>monocotyledons</xex>, is used as the
name of a large class of plants (the <class>Monocotyledones</class>, or
<class>Monocotyledonae</class>), and is generally understood to be
equivalent to the term <xex>endogens</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monocotyledones</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Monocotyledonae</ent>⟦br⟧
